text: well obviously I'm very disappointed for
me and for my team but I'm also
incredibly proud of the campaign that we
ran I think we did ourselves proud and
this was always going to be uphill for
us because I was someone who voted
remain we have a prime minister voters
remain and I think lots of conservative
party members felt that this was a
moment when you just had to have someone
who voted for brexit in the referendum
and that was in retrospect that was a
hurdle we were never able to overcome
but I think that being said there was a
lot of progress and you know I am
delighted for the country that Boris has
become Prime Minister I think he will be
a great Prime Minister he's got optimism
enthusiasm puts a smile on people's face
and he has total unshakable confidence
in our amazing country and that is a
quality that we need and you know we've
got some challenges ahead but Boris has
got that confidence and I think you'll
do a great job
